          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer30326167" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6173229564729705331">6.0 stars (One of My All Time Favorites). Absolutely outstanding debut novel. Right along side <a href='https://www.goodreads.com' rel='nofollow noopener'></a><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/127455.The_Lies_of_Locke_Lamora__Gentleman_Bastards___1_' title='The Lies of Locke Lamora (Gentleman Bastards, #1) by Scott Lynch' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Lies of Locke Lamora</a> by Scott Lynch and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com' rel='nofollow noopener'></a><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/186074.The_Name_of_the_Wind__Kingkiller_Chronicle___1_' title='The Name of the Wind (Kingkiller Chronicle, #1) by Patrick Rothfuss' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Name of the Wind</a> by Patrick Rothfuss as the best debut Fantasy novels of the last few years. This book is as good as the fantasy genre gets and I can not wait to read the sequel. Finally, IMHO, Glotka is one of the most original and best developed characters in a long time. Highly recommended. <br/><br/>Nominee: John A. Campbell Memorial Award for Best Novel (2008)</span>
  <span id="freeText6173229564729705331" style="display:none">6.0 stars (One of My All Time Favorites). Absolutely outstanding debut novel. Right along side <a href="https://www.goodreads.com" rel="nofollow noopener"></a><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/127455.The_Lies_of_Locke_Lamora__Gentleman_Bastards___1_" title="The Lies of Locke Lamora (Gentleman Bastards, #1) by Scott Lynch" rel="nofollow noopener">The Lies of Locke Lamora</a> by Scott Lynch and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com" rel="nofollow noopener"></a><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/186074.The_Name_of_the_Wind__Kingkiller_Chronicle___1_" title="The Name of the Wind (Kingkiller Chronicle, #1) by Patrick Rothfuss" rel="nofollow noopener">The Name of the Wind</a> by Patrick Rothfuss as the best debut Fantasy novels of the last few years. This book is as good as the fantasy genre gets and I can not wait to read the sequel. Finally, IMHO, Glotka is one of the most original and best developed characters in a long time. Highly recommended. <br /><br />Nominee: John A. Campbell Memorial Award for Best Novel (2008). </span>
  <a data-text-id="6173229564729705331" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


